This paper discusses the impact of different writing tasks on linguistic style, which is a topic related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the writing style, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of language models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on the impact of task framing on writing style could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
